(1, 'A valued client of Kforce is currently in need of a Full Stack/Software Developer with experience in Java. This position will sit remote but they need this resource to be near a local office in Memphis, Miami, or Buffalo. So if you are not near these places you would need to be open to relocate in the near future. NO C2C-PERM ROLE ONLY. NO Sponsorship provided for this role unfortunately. If this is not a direct fit please refer someone you may know. I would love to help, thanks. This company is hiring for (2) positions.\n\n(1 INTERVIEW TO HIRE)\n\nQualifications:\n• Full Stack Developer\n• 2-6+ years of experience in building web-based solutions and solid experience in designing or integrating RESTful APIs and business services for Java (JEE) platform supporting mission-critical business, security and compliance requirements\n• Knowledge of relational databases (preferably Oracle)\n• Deep understanding of the main RESTful APIs\n• Extensive experience with advanced source control systems (Git)\n• Experience with Spring Boot 2\n• Strong frontend application development experience with Angular 8 (not a must, it’s a plus)\n• Ability to learn and adapt quickly to new business domains and new technologies\n\n\nIf you are interested in this opportunity please provide me with your resume so we can further discuss. I look forward to speaking and connecting with you soon.', 'Alfred', 100000, 70000, '2021-03-14 17:13:32', 3, 'Software Engineer', 'CA', 'San Francisco'),
(2, 'The Manager, Database Administration is responsible for day-to-day governance and performance management of the DBA’s and systems under the management of the Guidewire Cloud Operations team. This role will assist in developing and implementing the strategic direction; managing the database systems by implementing policies and procedure for ensuring the security and integrity of the databases. This position will promote a customer care and service management philosophy that ensures customer satisfaction.\n\nJob role\nManage data base administrators (DBAs) supporting Oracle, MS SQL, PostgreSQL and MySQL Server Databases running in AWS.\nSetup, patching, debugging, upgrading and installation of databases and tool sets. Documents and maintains consistent and current patches across test development and production environments.\nContribute to data recovery, maintenance, data integrity, and space requirements for physical database being met through formulations and monitoring of policies, procedures, and standards relating to database management.\nAudit the current environments, provide capacity planning and best practices for the future production / development / test environments, which may include establishing new standards and procedures.\nManage Jira ticket queue and measure and promote efficiency in the processing and completion of tickets.\n\nResponsibilities\nDevelop strategies to maintain and support all databases with a goal to maximize availability and uptime.\nMaintain and improve best practices and standardize processes across the database team.\nIdentify opportunities for operational efficiency through innovation and integration.\nManage and contribute to data migration projects\nAnalyze and evaluate systems for consolidation, optimization, or operational efficiency.\nCo-manage the team and help them to achieve high levels of operational excellence.\nAuthor SOPs, configuration specifications and related technical documentation.\n\nKey Qualifying Skills\n10 or more years’ experience in managing Database Platforms (e.g. - Oracle, MS SQL, MySQL)\n2 or more years in a team leadership role with multiple reports\nPrior demonstrable technical experience having worked with multiple database products\nPL/SQL query language experience.\nKnowledge and experience in scripting languages, preferably e.g. - Shell, Python.\n\nEducation\nAn undergraduate or graduate level degree / diploma in Information Systems / Computer Science / EE or a related technical field of study from an accredited college or university or, an equivalent combination of relevant professional certifications and significant proven experience.\n\nAbout Guidewire\n\nGuidewire is the platform P&C insurers trust to engage, innovate, and grow efficiently.\n\nGuidewire combines core, data, digital, analytics, and AI to deliver our platform as a cloud service. More than 400 insurers, including the largest and most complex in the world, run on Guidewire.\n\nAs a partner to our customers, we continually evolve to enable their success. We are proud of our unparalleled implementation track record with 1000+ successful projects, supported by the largest R&D team and partner ecosystem in the industry. Our Marketplace provides hundreds of add-ons that accelerate integration, localization, and innovation.\n\nGuidewire Software, Inc. is proud to be an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer. We are committed to an inclusive workplace, and believe that a diversity of perspectives, abilities, and cultures is a key to our success. Qualified applicants will receive consideration without regard to race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, citizenship, marital status, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, veteran status, or disability. All offers are contingent upon passing a criminal history and other background checks where it\s applicable to the position.\n\nDisability Accommodations and Guidewire’s Appeals Process. Guidewire provides accommodations to the hiring process to create a fair opportunity for candidates with disabilities to contend for open positions. Accommodation requests should be directed to (650) 356-4940 or Accommodations@guidewire.com . If things do not go as hoped, we invite you to use our appeals process. Guidewire promises to independently review any denied accommodation and any decision not to offer you the position. The appeals process is the same in either case. Within five business days of receiving a notice of denial of an accommodation, or receiving a notice of your non-selection for a vacancy, call (650) 356-4940 or e-mail Accommodations@guidewire.com to make an appeal. Guidewire will assign a new decision-maker to review the request and/or hiring decision, who will then notify you in writing of a decision within 10 business days.', 'Charlie', 90000, 80000, '2021-03-14 17:13:32', 3, 'Database Manager', 'CA', 'San Francisco'),
(3, 'We are seeking a Nashville based mid-level SQL Server DB Engineer to join our Database Services team in Global Enterprise Technology Systems department.\n\nDatabase Management Services group develops consist of DB Engineering and DB Operations sub-groups. DB Operations group provides day-to-day operational support for AllianceBernstein’s DBMS environment. It works closely with application teams and oversees DBMS administration, maintenance and compliance. DB Engineering sub- group works on defining the roadmap for DBMS services, identifies and certifies new technologies beneficial for AB Businesses. The team is responsible for engineering new technical solutions, establishing operational standards, automating and optimizing DBMS support\n\nDescribe The Role\n\nMS SQL Server Engineer is a mid-level SQL Server DBA, who will act a subject matter expert for all platform related issues. The candidate will be responsible for developing new solutions, automating and optimizing SQL Server administration processes, and integrating Azure technologies into AB DBMS infrastructure. Knowledge of internal workings of the SQL Server and Azure technologies is essential. Very good programming skills (T-SQL, PowerShell, .Net) and good communication skills are absolute requirement. The environment is fast-paced and requires ability to learn fast, implement and hand-over to DB operations in a short cycle. The candidate must be able to work with application teams, advising on new technologies solving business problems. His role is essential in developing new utilities/scripts/programs helping with automation of standard operational tasks. The individual must be able to work independently and with other team members.\n\nDescribe the applications and business or enterprise functions the role supports:\n\nThe DB Engineer will be working mostly with Database Services team on automation, optimization of operational support of DBMS. He/she will also be providing expertise to different application teams in evaluating and certifying new technologies needed by business.\n\nThe key job responsibilities include, but are not limited to:\nDeveloping new and optimizing existing scripts/utilities/programs automating maintenance, administration, monitoring of SQL Server environments. That covers such areas as backup (native LogShipping, NetBackup, blob backup, etc…), HA/DR (Clusters, Azure Shared disk, AlwaysOn, SRDF), Performance monitoring (SCOM, SQLPerfMon, etc…), SSRS, SSIS, SSAS. Knowledge of PowerShell and T-SQL is essential\nExpanding functionality of internal DBMS management site with new functionality geared towards improving efficiency of operational DBMS support\nEvaluating and certifying new technologies, especially Azure PaaS services, such as Synapse, Managed Instance, DataFactory, containerization of SQL Server and Postgre, etc…\nDeveloping new performance monitoring solutions\nProviding subject matter expertise for SQL Server DBMS platform.\nWhat makes this role unique or interesting (if applicable)?\n\nThe most exciting part of the job is its dynamic and creative nature. The candidate will be working in a fast-paced environment with exposure to cutting edge technologies and challenges of adopting them. It is a big departure from a usual DBA role.\n\nWhat is the professional development value of this role, i.e. what learning and professional growth does the role offer the candidate?\n\nThe focus on finding right technical solutions to business problems provides opportunity to learn new technologies and new products, to develop creativity, to acquire project management skills, and to grow professionally. Interacting with a diverse group of professionals across all of GETS gives an exposure to intellectual and professional wealth of knowledge which is hard to underestimate\n\nQualifications\n\nJob Qualifications (The ideal candidate should have the following)\nExcellent knowledge of SQL Server technologies (SQL Server clustering, AlwaysON, LogShipping, SSIS, SSRS, etc.).\nExcellent programming skills with PowerShell and T-SQL, Knowledge of .Net is good to have\nWorking knowledge of any performance monitoring tools (such as SCOM, FogLight, etc…)\nGood knowledge of Windows platform\nKnowledge of Splunk and other logging technologies\nGood knowledge of Azure technologies (IaaS, PaaS, VM sizing, disk management, Runbooks, etc…)\nGood communication skills\n\nQualifications, Experience, Education\nThe candidate must have at least 5 years of SQL Server Engineering experience\nThe candidate must have BS in Computer Science or related areas\n\nSkills\nVery good knowledge of PowerShell, T-SQL is essential\nIn-depth knowledge of SQL Server (LogShipping, AlwasyOn, SSIS, SSRS, SSAS) is essential\nGood knowledge of Windows OS. Linux is optional\nKnowledge of Azure technologies\nKnowledge of SCOM and other monitoring software packages\nKnowledge of PostgreSQL – good to have', 'Delta', 110000, 90000, '2021-03-14 17:13:32', 3, 'SQL Server Database Engineer', 'CA', 'San Francisco');
